# Agent Stage Mapping

- PM Agent: intake, scope, acceptance criteria; set stage `pm`.
- Designer Agent: UX/content/design decisions only; set stage `designer`.
- Developer Agent: implementation only; set stage `developer`.
- QA Agent: verify acceptance criteria, responsiveness, console, regressions; set stage `qa`.
- Reviewer Agent: code quality/security/performance review; set stage `reviewer`.
- Only after QA pass + reviewer approval, move stage `done`.

If blocked, keep current stage and add a Hub note prefixed with `BLOCKED:`.
